  "body": "Running tests with lerna is very annoying because you have to scroll a lot to figure out which package actually had a failing test.\r\n\r\n*before*\r\n```\r\n// Package A\r\n✓ A1 Ok\r\nx A2 Error\r\n\r\n// Package B\r\n✓ B1 Ok\r\nx B2 Error\r\n```\r\n*after this PR*\r\n```\r\n✓ A1 Ok\r\n✓ B1 Ok\r\nx A2 Error\r\nx B2 Error\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Description**\r\n\r\nRun the unit tests across all packages with a single mocha run. If tests fail in multiple packages they will be nicely summarized at the end :+1: \r\n\r\n- Previous attempt https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/2988\r\n\r\n**TODO**\r\n- [ ] Make all tests work with the same preset, types and tsconfig options\r\n\r\n",
